                     <decoNote type="border">Fine historiated borders.</decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="histInit">Fine historiated initials. </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding notAfter="1500" notBefore="1400">
                        <p>15th-century English binding, blind-tooled in calf, by the <persName key="person_3672" role="bnd">'Scales' binder</persName> (N. Barker, 'A register of writs and the Scales binder', <title>The Book Collector</title> 21 (1972), 227-244, 356-79, no. 17 (p. 376)); rebacked, 17th century. For further discussion see N. Barker, 'Tanner 190 Revisited', in <title>Makers and Users of Medieval Books: Essays in Honour of A.S.G. Edwards</title>, ed. C. M. Meale and D. Pearsall, (2014)  78-88, and the Bodleian Library conservation report of October 2012 (=REFS. CXXXIV.1).</p>
                     </binding>
